Netstat, Curl, Ping, Traceroute - 

Send only 4 packets (Linux)
ping -c 4 google.com
*******************
TRACEROUTE – Trace the Path to a Server

Purpose:
Shows every hop (router) between your device and the destination.
***************************************
NETSTAT – Check Ports, Connections, and Listening Services

Purpose:

Show open ports

Show active connections

Check which service is using which port

Monitor network usage

❗ In new Linux versions, netstat is replaced by ss, but both work.
********************************************
ping	Test server availability & latency
traceroute	Show route path & hops
curl	Send HTTP requests / API testing
netstat	Show open ports & active connections
